{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "dra:first-timothy.4",
    "translationId": "dra",
    "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
    "chapterNumber": 4,
    "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4",
    "summary": "Source text for 1 Timothy 4 in Douay-Rheims Bible (Challoner)."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.1",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:1",
      "text": "Now the Spirit manifestly saith that in the last times some shall depart from the faith, giving heed to spirits of error and doctrines of devils,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.2",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:2",
      "text": "Speaking lies in hypocrisy and having their conscience seared,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.3",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:3",
      "text": "Forbidding to marry, to abstain from meats, which God hath created to be received with thanksgiving by the faithful and by them that have known the truth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.4",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:4",
      "text": "For every creature of God is good, and nothing to be rejected that is received with thanksgiving:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.5",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:5",
      "text": "For it is sanctified by the word of God and prayer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.6",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:6",
      "text": "These things proposing to the brethren, thou shalt be a good minister of Christ Jesus, nourished up in the words of faith and of the good doctrine which thou hast attained unto.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.7",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:7",
      "text": "But avoid foolish and old wives fables: and exercise thyself unto godliness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.8",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:8",
      "text": "For bodily exercise is profitable to little: but godliness is profitable to all things, having promise of the life that now is and of that which is to come.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.9",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:9",
      "text": "A faithful saying and worthy of all acceptation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.10",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:10",
      "text": "For therefore we labour and are reviled, because we hope in the living God, who is the Saviour of all men, especially of the faithful.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.11",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:11",
      "text": "These things command and teach:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.12",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:12",
      "text": "Let no man despise thy youth: but be thou an example of the faithful, in word, in conversation, in charity, in faith, in chastity.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.13",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:13",
      "text": "Till I come, attend unto reading, to exhortation and to doctrine.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.14",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:14",
      "text": "Neglect not the grace that is in thee, which was given thee by prophecy, with imposition of the hands of the priesthood.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.15",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:15",
      "text": "Meditate upon these things, be wholly in these things: that thy profiting may be manifest to all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "dra:first-timothy.4.16",
      "translationId": "dra",
      "bookSlug": "first-timothy",
      "chapterNumber": 4,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "1 Timothy 4:16",
      "text": "Take heed to thyself and to doctrine: be earnest in them. For in doing this thou shalt both save thyself and them that hear thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
